CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1973, pg. 25 reads: "Mission Baby Contest - Winners of the Eighth Annual Baby Contest, sponsored by the combined missionary societies of John Wesley AME Zion Church, rest in the arms of their staunchest supporters, their mothers. Stacey Lynn Harris, left, first prize winner, seems to be a bit amazed at her victory, while Yvette Mia Daniels, second prize winner tastes the tears of defeat.  Mrs. Rebecca Gray, extreme right, emcee for the afternoon, presents a cash award to the top place winner, while Dr. Virgil R. Hill, pastor of the church, looks on approvingly. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Stacey Lynn Harris, being held by mother, Dr. Virgil R. Hill,  Yvette Mia Daniels, being held by mother, and Rebecca Gray, in John Wesley AME Zion Church for baby contest
